fields.description:
I have seen this a number of times for fast running tasks. Example:
{noformat}
File ... was ignored because it was modified (2019-01-12 07:58:42.000) before task started (2019-01-12 07:58:42.135)
{noformat}

It looks like the time calculation should round down the start time of the task to the second so that file time comparisons works correctly since file times probably do not go to the milli-second level.

h3. Issue Summary
Some Bamboo licenses are being generated as Version 1 Licenses, which have fewer characters than Version 2 licenses, and can include the character {{<}} or {{>}}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add a Version 1 license to {{bamboo.cfg.xml}}
# Start Bamboo

h3. Expected Results
Bamboo starts as expected

h3. Actual Results

The below exception is thrown in the {{atlassian-bamboo.log}} file:
{noformat}
2019-01-03 19:51:53,733 FATAL [localhost-startStop-1] [BootstrapLoaderListener] An error was encountered while bootstrapping Bamboo (see below):
Could not find any valid decoders in [com.atlassian.extras.decoder.v2.Version2LicenseDecoder@16214fb7, com.atlassian.extras.decoder.v1.Version1LicenseDecoder@6f00ba8f] for license string <license string here>
com.atlassian.extras.decoder.api.LicenseDecoderNotFoundException: Could not find any valid decoders in [com.atlassian.extras.decoder.v2.Version2LicenseDecoder@16214fb7, com.atlassian.extras.decoder.v1.Version1LicenseDecoder@6f00ba8f] for license string <license string here>
{noformat}

h3. Workaround
Please ensure that the {{<}} or {{>}} characters are encoded, for example if your key includes the string:
{noformat}
ailuahfUaadbfaalaaussba<akaieiiqoqoqpah
{noformat}

Update it to
{noformat}
ailuahfUaadbfaalaaussba&lt;akaieiiqoqoqpah
{noformat}

Please also ensure that any whitespace (including spaces and carriage returns) in the key is kept as it was in [my.atlassian.com|https://my.atlassian.com].

h3. {color:#172b4d}Problem Definition{color}

{color:#172b4d}If a build fails, it's marked with a red exclamation mark on Bamboo's build dashboard. Then, in the right top corner under Run" shows up the option "Rerun failed/incomplete jobs only".{color}

{color:#172b4d}If a build passed on this page it's marked with a green hook and the related option repeat that build is then "Rerun this build".{color}

{color:#172b4d}In both re-run cases, the log information of the previous build (along with its build results) is lost. This is currently inevitable.{color}
h3. {color:#172b4d}Suggested Solution{color}

{color:#172b4d}Have a system property to disable{color} for this purpose. Alternatively, an option to keep a previous failure log even after a re-run would be helpful (especially for subsequent troubleshooting).
h3. Workaround

A feasible workaround is to hide the re-run button as shown in this Atlassian Community post: https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Bamboo-questions/Disable-re-build-option/qaq-p/887373
